                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.5034/6</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Representative <persName type="from"
                            >Rodgers</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-08-10T11:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 10, 1916, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>278. Order to notaries provides that information new corporations and
                    particularly those for exploration exploitation oil lands charter shall contain
                    clause providing that foreign stockholders renounce their national rights as to
                    company affairs, this meaning they waive all right to protection interest
                    through their national representatives. Informed that this has been tried before
                    but failed and is not considered to have legal effect. Nevertheless it is
                    undoubtedly dangerous and presumably contrary to treaty rights. Have filed
                    general protest.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rodgers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
